11:09.940 --> 11:12.044
AND YOU'RE
GONNA WANT TO FIRE ME.

11:12.080 --> 11:13.422
- YOU'RE CRAZY.
YOU'RE FIRED.

11:13.460 --> 11:16.111
NO WAY. THAT IS--THAT IS
THE WHOLE SECOND ACT.

11:16.150 --> 11:17.139
- THINK ABOUT IT.
THINK ABOUT IT.

11:17.190 --> 11:19.283
CUT THE FIRST TWO SCENES,
READ IT,

11:19.330 --> 11:21.912
AND YOU'LL SEE EVERYTHING
YOU NEED IS IN THERE.

11:21.950 --> 11:23.121
- BUT THERE'S--YOU
DON'T HAVE ALL THE INFORMATION.

11:23.160 --> 11:24.843
I'D HAVE TO REWS%R)K THE END OF--

11:24.890 --> 11:26.710
SO?
REWORK IT.

11:26.750 --> 11:28.365
OKAY.
WHAT IS THAT, THREE DAYS?

11:28.410 --> 11:29.718
- NO.
[scoffs]

11:29.750 --> 11:31.126
FOR YOU, MAYBE.

11:31.170 --> 11:32.307
- SARAH...

11:32.340 --> 11:35.924
THERE IS AN OPPORTUNITY
THAT HAS ARISEN

11:35.970 --> 11:40.725
THAT MIGHT GIVE YOU
A STAGED READING

11:40.760 --> 11:43.103
AT THE BERKELEY
TH EATER COMPANY.

11:43.150 --> 11:45.175
- NO.
- YEP.

11:45.220 --> 11:46.448
- [chuckles]
OKAY.

11:46.490 --> 11:48.936
THAT'S REALLY COOL,
BUT IT'S NOT READY.

11:48.980 --> 11:51.119
I SHOULD WAIT UNTIL
IT'S IN BETTER SHAPE.

11:51.150 --> 11:53.152
- YOU COULD DO THESE CHANGES
IN THREE DAYS.

11:53.190 --> 11:56.159
- I COULD IF I DIDN'T
HAVE A FAMILY AND A JOB.

11:56.190 --> 11:58.841
AND IT'S CLOSE, BUT--
- YOU KNOW I CAN'T HELP

11:58.890 --> 12:00.437
BUT THINK
WHAT WOULD HAPPEN

12:00.470 --> 12:02.859
IF YOU PUT ALL THAT
ENERGY YOU HAVE

12:02.890 --> 12:05.950
INTO THIS PLAY.

12:06.000 --> 12:07.820
SARAH...

12:07.860 --> 12:10.408
I HATE TO BE THE ONE
TO TELL YOU.

12:10.450 --> 12:13.510
YOU HAVE A GIFT.
YOU REALLY DO.

12:13.560 --> 12:16.893
THIS IS A GREAT PLAY.
THIS PLAY IS YOU.

12:16.940 --> 12:20.034
FOR ONCE IN YOUR LIFE,
LET YOURSELF COME FIRST.

12:24.120 --> 12:26.088
[doorbell rings]

12:28.360 --> 12:29.770
- HEY.
- HEY.

12:29.810 --> 12:31.368
- YOUR DAD HOME?
- YEAH.

12:36.200 --> 12:37.428
- HEY.
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

12:37.480 --> 12:39.050
WHAT THE HELL DO YOU WANT?

12:39.100 --> 12:41.568
- LOOK, I KNOW YOU'RE
PROBABLY SICK OF ME SAYING IT,

12:41.620 --> 12:44.271
BUT I'M SO SORRY.

12:44.310 --> 12:46.164
AND I HATE
THAT WE'RE NOT TALKING.

12:46.210 --> 12:47.279
- OKAY.
IS THAT IT?

12:47.310 --> 12:49.517
YOU DONE?
- NO, UM...

12:49.560 --> 12:51.243
I WANTED YOU TO KNOW
THAT I'M THINKING ABOUT

12:51.280 --> 12:53.032
BUYING A HOUSE.
- GREAT.

12:53.080 --> 12:55.139
WHAT DO YOU WANT?
YOU WANT TO BORROW SOME MONEY?

12:55.180 --> 12:56.386
BECAUSE YOU CAN'T.
SO YOU CAN GO.

12:56.430 --> 12:58.591
- NO, I DON'T--
I DON'T WANT TO BORROW MONEY.

12:58.630 --> 13:01.212
I KNOW YOU'RE PISSED
AND I TOTALLY UNDERSTAND,

13:01.260 --> 13:03.046
BUT YOU KNOW...

13:03.090 --> 13:04.227
NORMALLY,
YOU WOULD'VE SAID MAYBE,

13:04.260 --> 13:06.228
"THAT'S INTERESTING,
WHY NOW?

13:06.260 --> 13:08.296
YOU DON'T HAVE
A FIANCEE OR A SON ANYMORE."

13:08.330 --> 13:10.059
- MM-HMM.
- TO WHICH I WOULD REPLY,

13:10.090 --> 13:12.194
"THAT'S HOW I'M GONNA
WIN THEM BACK."

13:13.370 --> 13:15.372
- OKAY.
WELL, YOU REALLY ARE AN IDIOT.

13:15.410 --> 13:17.139
- YOU DON'T THINK
IT'S A GOOD IDEA?

13:17.170 --> 13:19.058
- NO, I DON'T.
YOU'RE BEHAVING LIKE A CHILD.

13:19.100 --> 13:20.988
YOU CHEATED ON YOUR FIANCEE,
AND NOW YOU THINK THAT

13:21.040 --> 13:23.031
GOING AND BUYING A HOUSE
IS GONNA MAKE IT ALL BETTER?

13:23.070 --> 13:26.142
I MEAN, SERIOUSLY?
THAT'S YOUR PLAN?

13:26.180 --> 13:28.626
- ACTUALLY, YEAH, THAT'S
THE PLAN AS OF RIGHT NOW.

13:28.660 --> 13:30.139
- WELL, THAT'S
A STUPID PLAN, OKAY?

13:30.180 --> 13:31.112
AND IT'S
FURTHER PROOF TO ME

13:31.150 --> 13:33.038
THAT YOU ARE IMMATURE
AND IRRESPONSIBLE.

13:33.080 --> 13:34.217
- OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT,
I SCREWED UP.

13:34.260 --> 13:35.079
I CHEATED ON MY FIANCEE

13:35.120 --> 13:36.564
AND I RUINED THINGS
HERE FOR YOU.

13:36.600 --> 13:37.976
- YOU SURE DID.
- AND I'M SORRY ABOUT THAT.

13:38.020 --> 13:39.328
BUT THAT DOESN'T
MEAN EVERY SINGLE DECISION

13:39.370 --> 13:42.055
I MAKE NOW IS STUPID
OR IMMATURE, ALL RIGHT?

13:42.090 --> 13:43.193
HAVE YOU EVER NIOADE A MISTAKE?

13:43.230 --> 13:45.403
NO, I HAVEN'T, ACTUALLY.
I NEVER HAVE MADE A MISTAKE.

13:45.440 --> 13:47.123
NOT LIKE THAT,
OKAY?

13:47.170 --> 13:48.546
SO GO BUY YOUR HOUSE
AND MAKE YOUR LIFE ALL BETTER.

13:48.580 --> 13:50.548
- OKAY, I'LL BUY THE HOUSE.
- GOOD, GO BUY IT.

13:50.580 --> 13:51.956
- GREAT.
- OKAY.

13:52.000 --> 13:53.069
- FINE.
- LEAVE ME OUT OF IT.

13:53.100 --> 13:54.476
- YEAH.

13:54.520 --> 13:56.511
THANK YOU.
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

14:06.010 --> 14:07.250
- PERFECT.
- [glggleSJ

14:07.290 --> 14:09.178
- I WENT TO SCHOOL FOR IT.
I'M NOT KIDDING.

14:09.220 --> 14:10.972
OH, HEY THERE,
TONYA HARDING.

14:11.020 --> 14:12.351
- I'M A REALLY GOOD SKATER.
- UH-HUH.

14:12.400 --> 14:13.424
- AM I NOT
A REALLY GOOD SKATER?

14:13.470 --> 14:15.153
- NO, YOU ARE
A GOOD SKATER.

14:15.190 --> 14:16.987
YOU ONLY FELL ONCE.
- I ONLY FELL ONCE!

14:17.020 --> 14:18.669
AND IT WASN'T EVEN
A BAD FALL.

14:18.710 --> 14:20.598
IT WAS JUST
SOME FREAK ACCIDENT.

14:20.650 --> 14:22.993
I GOTTA GET CHECKED OUT
FOR OSTEOPOROSIS.

14:23.030 --> 14:25.476
HEY, DID MY DAD CALL
ABOUT MY OLD GOLF CLUBS FOR SYD?

14:25.510 --> 14:26.989
- I HAVEN'T HEARD.

14:27.030 --> 14:29.999
- WELL, SYD, DO YOU KNOW WHAT
WE ARE DOING TODAY?

14:30.040 --> 14:32.099
- TODAY'S MY PLAYDATE
WITH CHLOE.

14:32.140 --> 14:34.279
- MAYBE JUST THIS ONCE
WE CAN RESCHEDULE CHLOE,

14:34.320 --> 14:37.073
BECAUSE I HAVE
SOMETHING SO SPECIAL

14:37.110 --> 14:38.179
PLANNED FOR YOU AND ME.

14:38.220 --> 14:40.381
- WELL, I THOUGHT
WE HAD SPECIAL TIME YESTERDAY.

14:40.430 --> 14:43.456
AND THE DAY BEFORE THAT.
- RIGHT.

14:43.500 --> 14:45.661
WELL, TODAY
WE'RE GOING TO THE ZOO

14:45.710 --> 14:47.985
BECAUSE THEY HAVE
BABY KOMODO DRAGONS.

14:48.020 --> 14:49.226
- COOL!

14:49.260 --> 14:50.943
- GET YOUR BAG, LET'S GO.
- OKAY.

14:52.680 --> 14:54.432
- [chuckles]

14:59.070 --> 15:00.571
- IT'S A FACT THAT THINGS
GET OUT OF CONTROL

15:00.620 --> 15:02.099
ON PROM NIGHT,
AND I'M JUST ASKING YOU TO

15:02.140 --> 15:03.960
REALLY TALK TO HER, THAT'S ALL.
- I DID TALK TO HER.

15:04.000 --> 15:05.103
WE WENT OVER THE RULES
FOR PROM NIGHT,

15:05.140 --> 15:06.653
AND HER CURFEW'S
GONNA BE AN HOUR LATER,

15:06.690 --> 15:08.271
WHICH IS TOTALLY FINE.
- HONEY--

15:08.320 --> 15:09.719
- IF SHE WANTS TO GO
TO AN AFTER-PARTY, LET HER.

15:09.770 --> 15:11.032
- "IF" SHE WANTS
TO GO TO AN AFTER-PARTY?

15:11.080 --> 15:12.035
HONEY, THAT'S BEING NAIVE.

15:12.080 --> 15:14.002
- IT'S NOT BEING NAIVE.
- IT IS BEING NAIVE.

15:14.050 --> 15:15.187
HONEY, OF COURSE SHE'S
GONNA GO TO AN AFTER-PARTY.

15:15.220 --> 15:17.632
- I LAID OUT THE RULES.
- I HAD SEX WITH MICHELLE MCCANN

15:17.670 --> 15:19.285
ON PROM NIGHT.
- I KNOW YOU DID, OKAY?

15:19.330 --> 15:20.399
- OKAY.

15:20.430 --> 15:21.226
- BUT I HATE TO POINT
IT OUT TO YOU.

15:21.260 --> 15:22.352
KIDS ARE GONNA HAVE SEX
NO MATTER

15:22.400 --> 15:23.219
IF IT'S PROM NIGHT OR NOT.

15:23.260 --> 15:25.057
- NO, NO, NO, HONEY.
- YES, THEY ARE.

15:25.090 --> 15:26.159
- IT'S DIFFERENT. NO, IT'S NOT.
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

15:26.200 --> 15:27.428
DO YOU KNOW WHAT I REMEMBER
ABOUT MY PROM NIGHT?

15:27.470 --> 15:29.051
- WHAT?
- NOTHING.

15:29.100 --> 15:30.362
ABSOLUTELY NOTHING.

15:30.410 --> 15:32.059
I DON'T REMEMBER
WHAT HER DRESS LOOKED LIKE.

15:32.100 --> 15:33.499
I DON'T REMEMBER
WHAT COLOR IT WAS.

15:33.550 --> 15:35.199
I DON'T REMEMBER
WHAT HER PARENTS LOOKED LIKE.

15:35.240 --> 15:37.162
I DON'T REMEMBER
WHERE I PUT THE CORSAGE.

15:37.210 --> 15:39.098
- OH, MY GOD, OKAY.
- HONEY, I WAS LIKE A ZOMBIE

15:39.140 --> 15:40.300
WITH ONE DIRECT IVE--

15:40.350 --> 15:41.965
TO GET
MICHELLE MCCANN'S DRESS OFF.

15:42.010 --> 15:44.149
- GREAT.
- I DO REMEMBER ONE THING.

15:44.180 --> 15:45.624
SHE HAD A DRESS
WITH A SLIT UP TO HERE.

15:45.660 --> 15:46.763
- I KNOW, I REMEMBER.
- UP TO HERE, HONEY.

15:46.800 --> 15:47.903
- I SAW THE PICTURES, I KNOW.

15:47.940 --> 15:49.521
- I'M DOWN ON MY KNEES,
TAKING OFF HER GARTER BELT.

15:49.560 --> 15:50.970
- I DON'T WANT TO HEAR THIS
RIGHT NOW.

15:51.010 --> 15:52.045
I DON'T WANT TO HEAR
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING.

15:52.080 --> 15:53.661
STOP.
- I WANT TO MAKE A POINT.

15:53.710 --> 15:55.086
I WANT YOU TO
REALLY TALK TO OUR DAUGHTER.

15:55.120 --> 15:56.348
- HADDIE
IS NOT MICHELLE MCCANN,

15:56.400 --> 15:58.186
AND I WILL TALK TO HER.

15:58.230 --> 16:01.984
- THANK YOU.

16:02.030 --> 16:03.406
[footsteps approaching]

16:03.440 --> 16:04.532
- HEY.
- HI.

16:04.580 --> 16:06.059
- CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND?

16:06.100 --> 16:07.988
- AH.
I WOULD LOVE TO

16:08.030 --> 16:09.713
BUT I'M WORKING,

16:09.760 --> 16:13.230
AND I'VE BEEN INSTRUCTED
TO PUT MYSELF FIRST.

16:13.280 --> 16:15.726
- OKAY, COULD YOU
PUT YOURSELF FIRST

16:15.760 --> 16:17.728
IN, LIKE, TWO MINUTES
AFTER WE TALK?

16:17.760 --> 16:21.002
I TRIED TO TALK TO ADAM,
BUT HE HATES MY GUTS.

16:21.040 --> 16:22.416
- SORRY, CROS.

16:22.460 --> 16:24.735
YOU DID SLEEP WITH
HIS CHILD'S BEHAVIORAL AIDE.

16:24.770 --> 16:26.761
- YEAH, IT SOUNDS SO SCANDALOUS
THE WAY YOU SAY IT.

16:26.810 --> 16:28.118
- NO, I KNOW.
IT'S DEFINITELY

16:28.150 --> 16:30.084
THE WAY IT SOUNDS
THAT WAS SCAN DALOUS

16:30.120 --> 16:31.257
'CAUSE DOING IT,
NO BIG DEAL.

16:31.300 --> 16:33.814
- SARAH, I'M NOT DENYING
WHAT A JERK I AM.

16:33.850 --> 16:36.398
I TAKE
FULL RESPONSIBILITY.

16:36.440 --> 16:39.091
I DON'T KNOW WHAT ELSE
YOU'D LIKE ME TO SAY.

16:39.130 --> 16:42.122
- I'M SORRY.
IT JUST PISSES ME OFF.

16:42.170 --> 16:45.025
- WELL, I--

16:45.070 --> 16:47.061
I CAME OVER BECAUSE

16:47.100 --> 16:48.203
I'M GONNA
SELL THE HOUSEBOAT,

16:48.240 --> 16:50.720
AND I'M GONNA USE THAT MONEY
TO PUT A DOWN PAYMENT

16:50.760 --> 16:52.762
ON A HOUSE
IN HOPES THAT

16:52.800 --> 16:55.075
JASMINE WILL WANT TO
COME LIVE IN IT WITH ME.

16:55.110 --> 16:56.759
- WHAT?

16:56.800 --> 16:59.803
YOU'RE GONNA BUY A HOUSE
SHE'S NEVER SEEN

16:59.840 --> 17:01.660
TO TRY TO WIN HER BACK?
- LOOK, I DON'T--

17:01.710 --> 17:03.086
I DON'T KNOW WHAT ELSE
TO DO.

17:03.120 --> 17:03.939
I WOULD DO ANYTHING.

17:03.980 --> 17:05.629
IF I THOUGHT
SHE WANTED AN AIRPLANE,

17:05.670 --> 17:07.490
I WOULD FIGURE OUT
HOW TO GET HER AN AIRPLANE.

17:07.540 --> 17:09.747
SO I THOUGHT
MAYBE YOU COULD COME BY

17:09.780 --> 17:12.089
AND GIVE ME, LIKE, YOU KNOW,
A FEMALE'S PERSPECTIVE

17:12.130 --> 17:14.678
ON WHETHER SHE'LL THINK
IT'S CUTE OR NICE,

17:14.720 --> 17:16.688
AND YOU KNOW,
IF SHE WOULD LIKE IT.

17:16.720 --> 17:18.859
- I'VE NEVER BOUGHT A HOUSE,

17:18.890 --> 17:20.778
BUT I AM A FEMALE.

17:20.830 --> 17:22.821
SO YES, I CAN DO THAT.

17:22.860 --> 17:24.487
- THANK YOU.

17:24.520 --> 17:26.067
- I DON'T KNOW
IF IT'LL WORK, BUT IT'S--

17:26.110 --> 17:28.203
IT'S A GRAND GESTURE.

17:28.250 --> 17:30.286
- IT'LL BE GREAT TOO
IF MAYBE, YOU KNOW,

17:30.320 --> 17:32.481
JULIA AND JOEL--
- YEAH, AND ADAM.

17:35.500 --> 17:38.389
- I DON'T THINK
ADAM'S EVER GONNA COME OVER.

17:46.650 --> 17:48.220
- WELL, I'LL BE THERE.

17:50.620 --> 17:53.509
- HEY, HONEY, I THINK WE SHOULD
TRY ON THE GREEN ONE FIRST.

17:53.550 --> 17:54.778
- I'M TRYING
ON THE PURPLE ONE.

17:54.830 --> 17:56.548
- FOUND A LITTLE BLUE ONE
THAT MIGHT WORK.

17:56.590 --> 17:58.581
- OKAY.
- IT'S A LOT SHORTER,

17:58.620 --> 18:00.247
BUT IT'S STILL
KINDA CUTE AND FLIRTY.

18:00.280 --> 18:02.202
IT'S A LITTLE SHORT,
THOUGH.

18:02.250 --> 18:04.798
HEY, HONEY, DID YOU GUYS
TALK ABOUT YOUR PLANS

18:04.840 --> 18:06.728
FOR AFTER PROM?

18:06.770 --> 18:08.522
- NO, I SAID
I WOULD CALL YOU, RIGHT?

18:08.570 --> 18:10.117
- I KNOW, BUT I JUST--
I NEED TO KNOW

18:10.150 --> 18:11.526
IF ANY OF YOUR FRIENDS
ARE GETTING HOTEL ROOMS,

18:11.570 --> 18:13.117
SO I KNOW WHERE TO
PICK YOU UP.

18:13.160 --> 18:14.730
- MOM, NO,
THEY'RE NOT, OKAY?

18:14.780 --> 18:16.771
- [gasp5]

18:16.810 --> 18:18.459
HONEY, YOU LOOK STUNNING.

18:18.510 --> 18:19.909
- NO.
- IT IS SO PRETTY.

18:19.960 --> 18:21.359
- I LOOK LIKE--
- I DIDN'T THINK THE PURPLE

18:21.410 --> 18:22.786
WOULD WORK,
BUT IT WORKS WITH THE JEWELS,

18:22.820 --> 18:24.469
AND IT'S LIKE
A YOUNG ELIZABETH TAYLOR.

18:24.510 --> 18:25.818
- NO, I DON'T.
I DON'T LIKE IT.

18:25.860 --> 18:29.091
- ARE YOU AND ALEX
TALKING ABOUT SEX?

18:30.210 --> 18:31.370
I JUST HAD TO ASK.

18:31.420 --> 18:33.559
- NO, MOM.

18:33.590 --> 18:34.796
- OKAY.

18:34.830 --> 18:36.889
OKAY, I JUST WONDERED.

18:36.940 --> 18:39.864
- PROM NIGHT IS A CLICHE NIGHT
TO HAVE SEX, OKAY?

18:39.910 --> 18:41.241
- I AGREE.
HONEY, AS A MOM, I JUST

18:41.290 --> 18:42.837
HAVE TO ASK THESE
QUESTIONS, I'M SORRY.

18:42.880 --> 18:44.529
- YEAH, WHATEVER.
IT'S COOL.

18:44.570 --> 18:46.219
- YOU LOOK AMAZING.

18:46.260 --> 18:49.491
I MEAN, I'M NOT KIDDING.
YOU LOOK STUNNING.

18:49.540 --> 18:50.700
- I'M GONNA
TRY ON SOMETHING ELSE.

18:50.750 --> 18:52.889
- ALL RIGHT.
TRY ON THE GREEN.

18:52.920 --> 18:54.364
THE DARK--

18:54.400 --> 18:57.403
I CAN...BRING IT IN.

18:59.860 --> 19:01.851
OKAY.

19:09.760 --> 19:12.627
- HEY.
- HEY.

19:12.660 --> 19:14.662
- THIS JUST IN...
I'M NOT COOKING.

19:14.700 --> 19:16.383
- I'M SO SURPRISED.

19:16.430 --> 19:19.354
- MEDIOCRE PIZZA
OR TRULY TERRIBLE CHINESE?

19:19.390 --> 19:21.460
- OOH, CHINESE, 'CAUSE
IT'S THE TONGUE TWISTER.

19:21.500 --> 19:22.637
- [chuckles]

19:22.670 --> 19:23.944
WHAT'S ALL THIS?

19:23.990 --> 19:26.458
- JUST A BUNCH
OF NANA'S OLD DRESSES.

19:26.510 --> 19:27.989
- OH, YEAH?
AW.

19:28.020 --> 19:31.979
WHAT FOR?
- WELL...DON'T LAUGH.

19:32.030 --> 19:33.338
PROM.

19:33.370 --> 19:34.997
- [laughing]

19:35.030 --> 19:37.442
- SEE, I TOLD YOU
NOT TO LAUGH IN MY FACE.

19:37.480 --> 19:39.721
- YOU'RE KIDDING!
- I'M NOT KIDDING.

19:39.760 --> 19:41.967
I CAN EXPLAIN,
SO IF YOU'LL HOLD

19:42.000 --> 19:44.275
YOUR HYSTERICAL LAUGHTER
UNTIL THE END.

19:44.320 --> 19:46.891
HADDIE AND HER BOYFRIEND ARE,
LIKE, BEGGING ME TO GO,

19:46.940 --> 19:50.626
AND SO I THOUGHT
IT WOULD BE FUNNY TO GO.

19:50.670 --> 19:52.945
AND YOU KNOW, WHATEVER.
- WHO IS YOUR DATE?

19:52.980 --> 19:54.971
- I DON'T KNOW.
SOME GUY THAT ALEX KNOWS

19:55.020 --> 19:56.840
FROM THE COMMUNITY CENTER.

19:56.880 --> 19:58.871
- YOU'RE GOING TO PROM
ON A BLIND DATE!

19:58.920 --> 20:01.741
IT'S, LIKE, 1954.
- SO WEIRD.

20:01.780 --> 20:03.953
IT'S STUPID.
- I MEAN, IT'S NOT STUPID.

20:03.990 --> 20:05.878
I LOVE IT.
I'M SO EXCITED!

20:05.920 --> 20:08.992
I MEAN, OF COURSE IT'S DUMB,
IT'S DORKY, IT'S CORNY.

20:09.030 --> 20:09.849
- IT IS.
- IT'S PROM.

20:09.890 --> 20:13.235
BUT IT'S A STORY
YOU'LL ALWAYS TELL.

20:13.280 --> 20:16.659
IT'S AN EXPERIENCE
YOU WON'T BE SORRY YOU HAD

20:16.690 --> 20:17.964
NO MATTER
IF IT'S GOOD OR BAD.

20:18.000 --> 20:21.834
AND IT'S JUST
A BEAUTIFUL, SENTIMENTAL WAY

20:21.870 --> 20:22.859
TO SAY GOOD-BYE
TO HIGH SCHOOL

20:22.910 --> 20:24.662
AND I LOVE
THAT YOU'RE DOING IT.

20:27.670 --> 20:29.592
SO WHAT, ARE YOU
GONNA CUT ONE OF THESE UP?

20:29.640 --> 20:32.325
REALLY, GIVE IT A PRETTY IN PINK
KIN DA TREATMENT?

20:32.360 --> 20:33.918
DON'T ACT LIKE
YOU HAVEN'T SEEN IT.

20:33.950 --> 20:35.394
- YOU'RE DATING YOURSELF.

20:35.440 --> 20:36.816
- WELL, I HOPE
YOU'RE A LADIES MAN,

20:36.850 --> 20:39.364
BECAUSE THIS BOAT
IS A BIT OF A LURE

20:39.410 --> 20:41.025
FOR ATTRACTIVE LADIES.

20:41.060 --> 20:43.028
- SOUNDS SWEET.
- IT'S, UH...

20:43.060 --> 20:44.789
QUITE A VESSEL.
- SWEET.

20:44.820 --> 20:45.957
- BUCKLE UP.
- ALL RIGHT.

20:46.000 --> 20:47.399
- ALL RIGHT, MAN.

20:47.450 --> 20:48.724
UM, WHAT ELSE?
OH.

20:48.760 --> 20:50.796
I WOULDN'T KEEP
ANYTHING OUT HERE THAT RUSTS.

20:50.830 --> 20:52.513
THIS MIST IS REALLY DAMP.

20:52.560 --> 20:54.824
AND I'D KEEP THE MUSIC DOWN,

20:54.870 --> 20:56.906
'CAUSE IT
